:INFO
What Is Lion's Mane and Why Grow It at Home
Lion's mane is a culinary and medicinal mushroom prized for its tender texture and \
potential cognitive benefits. Growing it at home costs a fraction of retail prices \
and delivers fresh flushes within two to three weeks of inoculation.

:COUNTER.half
12 Days to First Flush
|
:COUNTER.half
85% Humidity Target

:INFO
Substrate: Hardwood Sawdust and Wheat Bran
Lion's mane grows best on a mix of hardwood sawdust and wheat bran, typically at an \
80 to 20 ratio by dry weight. The bran adds nitrogen and accelerates mycelium growth. \
Pasteurise or sterilise the mix before inoculation to eliminate competing moulds.

:CHECKLIST
Beginner Equipment
Polypropylene grow bags
Pressure cooker (23 litre minimum)
Lion's mane grain spawn
Hardwood sawdust
Wheat bran
Isopropyl alcohol (70%)
Spray bottle for misting
Thermometer and hygrometer
Humidity tent or Martha shelf

:INFO
Fruiting Conditions to Dial In
Once fully colonised, move the block to fruiting conditions: 18 to 24 degrees Celsius, \
indirect light for 12 hours a day, fresh air exchanges four to six times daily, and \
relative humidity between 80 and 90 percent. Mist the surface without soaking it.

:QUOTE
Harvest the moment the teeth form. One day too late and the bitterness is already there.

:PATH
Inoculation
Introducing mushroom spawn into the prepared substrate so the mycelium can begin growing.

:PATH
Colonisation (10–14 days)
The mycelium spreads throughout the substrate, establishing a strong network.

:PATH
Fruiting Initiation
Environmental conditions trigger the mycelium to begin forming mushroom pins.

:PATH
First Flush Harvest
The first batch of mature mushrooms is ready and harvested.

:PATH
Second Flush Recovery
The substrate recovers and produces another round of mushrooms.

:NOTE
Contamination is the most common failure point for new growers. Green, black, \
or pink patches on the block indicate Trichoderma or Penicillium mould. Remove \
the block from your grow space immediately and seal it before disposal. Do not \
open the bag near other blocks. Keep your inoculation area clean and work fast.
